---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config';
import { rotateCTA } from '../utils/cta';
const cta = rotateCTA('quick-cash-home-buyers');
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Quick Cash Home Buyers in Arizona — Close in 7-21 Days | Cash Guy Nate"
  description="Quick cash home buyers serving Phoenix, Tucson, Mesa, and AZ statewide. 7-21 day close, no fees, no repairs. Same-day quote. (602) 555-0100."
  pageType="service"
  crumbs={[{ label: "Home", href: "/" }, { label: "Quick Cash Home Buyers" }]}
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="hero__kicker">Phoenix · Tucson · Statewide Arizona</span>
      <h1>Quick Cash Home Buyers Serving Arizona</h1>
      <p class="hero__sub">We're a local Phoenix-based investor team buying houses in Arizona since 2018. Same-day quotes, written offers in 24 hours, closes in 7-21 days. Real cash, real timelines, no surprises.</p>
      <a href={`tel:${SITE.phone}`} class="btn btn--large">{cta}</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container container--narrow">
    <h2>What makes a cash buyer "quick"</h2>
    <p>
      The word "quick" in the cash-buyer market can mean very different things. Quick offer? Quick written contract? Quick close? The differences matter because they're not always all from the same buyer.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Quick offer:</strong> We deliver a verbal quote on the first call (5 minutes). Most operators do this; it's table stakes.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Quick written contract:</strong> Written purchase agreement within 24-48 hours of the property walk-through. Independent investors typically deliver this. iBuyers and franchises may take longer.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Quick close:</strong> Closing in 7-14 days from contract signing. This is the part most operators stretch. We close in this range on clean-title properties; longer for properties with title complications, probate, or short-sale situations.
    </p>
    <p>
      We aim to be quick in all three senses.
    </p>

    <h2>Why our timelines are faster than typical</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>One decision-maker.</strong> When you call, you talk to the same person who walks the property and signs the offer. No back-and-forth with a "specialist" or escalation to corporate approval. Decisions get made on the call.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Pre-funded.</strong> We close cash from our own capital, not from a loan against the property. There's no underwriting, no lender approval, no appraisal contingency. Title work alone determines the timeline.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Standard contract.</strong> We use an Arizona-standard purchase agreement with a few investor-specific clauses. Your attorney can review it in 30 minutes. No 50-page custom contracts that take a week to read.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Title relationships.</strong> We've worked with the major AZ title companies enough that our paperwork moves through their system without unusual delays. Title commitments typically arrive in 5-10 business days.
    </p>

    <h2>Timeline by scenario</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Owner-occupied, clean title, no HOA:</strong> 7-10 business days from contract to close</li>
      <li><strong>Owner-occupied, mortgage payoff, no HOA:</strong> 10-14 business days</li>
      <li><strong>Owner-occupied with HOA:</strong> 14-21 business days (HOA estoppels are typically the slow part)</li>
      <li><strong>Estate / inherited property in active probate:</strong> 30-60 days (court approval timeline)</li>
      <li><strong>Short sale (lender approval required):</strong> 60-120 days (lender's timeline drives this)</li>
      <li><strong>Tenant-occupied rental:</strong> Same as owner-occupied; we honor existing leases</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What can slow even a "quick" cash sale</h2>
    <p>
      Honest list of things that add days:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>IRS liens or judgment liens against the seller</li>
      <li>Old utility easements that require title cleanup</li>
      <li>HOA management companies that take 15+ days to issue estoppels</li>
      <li>Mortgage payoff demands from slow lenders (some are 14-21 days)</li>
      <li>Deceased prior owners in chain of title without proper transfer</li>
      <li>Multi-state heir scenarios in estate sales</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We discover most of these during title work in the first 3-7 days. If something will slow the close, we tell you immediately and revise timing expectations.
    </p>

    <h2>What we work in</h2>
    <p>
      Phoenix metro (Phoenix, Mesa, Tempe, Scottsdale, Chandler, Gilbert, Glendale, Peoria, Surprise, Buckeye, Avondale, Goodyear, Casa Grande, and all the surrounding cities). Tucson metro. Outlying AZ cities (Flagstaff, Prescott, Sierra Vista, Yuma, Kingman, Apache Junction, Queen Creek, Lake Havasu City, Bullhead City). We work statewide AZ.
    </p>

    <h2>How to start</h2>
    <p>
      Call (602) 555-0100. We answer Mon-Sat 8am-8pm. Five minutes on the phone, same-day quote range, walk-through within 24-72 hours, written offer within 24 hours of the walk.
    </p>
    <div class="inline-disclaimer">
      <strong>Cash buyer disclosure:</strong> {SITE.brandName} buys as a principal investor — not a broker. Offers are typically below open-market value in exchange for speed and certainty.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <h2>Ready to start?</h2>
      <p>Five minutes is enough for a real quote. Same-day callback if we miss the first ring.</p>
      <a href={`tel:${SITE.phone}`} class="btn btn--large">Call {SITE.phoneDisplay}</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
